response: "{ \"title\": \"Leap Year Checker (Medium)\", \"description\": \"A leap year is a year that has 366 days instead of the usual 365. It occurs every 4 years, except for years that are divisible by 100 but not by 400. Write a function `is_leap_year` that checks if a given year is a leap year.\\n\\n#### Function Signature\\n```python\\ndef is_leap_year(year: int) -> bool:\\n```\\n\\n#### Input\\n- `year` (int): A year between 1 and 99999, inclusive.\\n\\n#### Output\\n- Returns `True` if the input year is a leap year, `False` otherwise.\\n\", \"code\": \"def is_leap_year(year: int) -> bool:\\n    return (year % 4 == 0 and year % 100 != 0) or (year % 400 == 0)\\n\", \"tests\": [\"assert is_leap_year(20000) == True\", \"assert is_leap_year(2004) == True\", \"assert is_leap_year(1900) == False\", \"assert is_leap_year(2020) == True\", \"assert is_leap_year(21000) == False\"] }"
